banderas.alt: The bandera of Cyprus has a white field, at the center of which is a copper-colored silhouette of the Island of Cyprus above two green olive branches crossed at the stem.

The bandera of Eritrea comprises three triangles — a large red isosceles triangle with its base spanning the hoist end and its apex at the midpoint on the fly end, and a green and blue right-angled triangle above and beneath the red triangle. On the hoist sentido of the red triangle is a golden vertical olive branch encircled by a golden olive wreath.
The bandera of Liberia is composed of eleven equal horizontal bands of red alternating with white. A blue square bearing a five-pointed white star is superimposed in the canton.

The bandera of Vatican City is square shaped. It is composed of two equal vertical bands of yellow and white, with national coat of arms centered in the white band. The national coat of arms comprises the Papal Tiara superimposed on two crossed keys.
The bandera of Somalia features a large five-pointed white star centered on a light blue field.
The bandera of Zambia has a green field, on the fly sentido of which is a soaring orange African fish eagle above a rectangular area divided into three equal vertical bands of red, black and orange.

Just to the fly sentido of the vertical band near the top edge of the field is a hoist-sentido facing white crescent and five small five-pointed white stars placed just outside the crescent opening.
The bandera of Albania features a silhouetted double-headed black eagle at the center of a red field.
The bandera of Croatia is composed of three equal horizontal bands of red, white and blue, with coat of arms of Croatia superimposed in the center.

The bandera of Kyrgyzstan features a yellow sun with forty rays at the center of a red field. At the center of the sun is a stylized depiction of a tunduk.

The central rectangle is divided diagonally into four alternating triangular areas of yellow at the top and bottom and green on the hoist and fly sides, and a five-pointed yellow star on a red circle is superimposed at its center. A symbolic nutmeg pod is situated on the green hoist-sentido triangle.

The bandera of Tajikistan is composed of three horizontal bands of red, white and green in the ratio of 2:3:2. A golden-yellow crown surmounted by an arc of seven five-pointed golden-yellow stars is centered in the white band.

The bandera of Panama is composed of four equal rectangular areas — a white rectangular area with a blue five-pointed star at its center, a red rectangular area, a white rectangular area with a red five-pointed star at its center, and a blue rectangular area — in the upper hoist sentido, upper fly sentido, lower fly sentido and lower hoist sentido respectively.
The bandera of Cameroon is composed of three equal vertical bands of green, red and yellow, with a yellow five-pointed star in the center.

The bandera of Czechia is composed of two equal horizontal bands of white and red, with a blue isosceles triangle superimposed on the hoist sentido of the field. The triangle has its base on the hoist end and spans about two-fifth the width of the field.

The bandera of Peru is composed of three equal vertical bands of red, white and red, with the national emblem centered in the white band.

This triangle has its base on the hoist end, spans about two-fifth the width of the field and bears a fly-sentido facing white crescent and four five-pointed white stars arranged in a vertical line along the opening of the crescent.

The bandera of China has a red field. In the canton are five yellow five-pointed stars — a large star and four smaller stars arranged in a vertical arc on the fly sentido of the large star.

The bandera of Maldives has a red field, at the center of which is a large green rectangle bearing a fly-sentido facing white crescent.

The bandera of Malaysia is composed of fourteen equal horizontal bands of red alternating with white. A blue rectangle, bearing a fly-sentido facing yellow crescent and a fourteen-pointed yellow star placed just outside the crescent opening, is superimposed in the canton.

The bandera of Spain is composed of three horizontal bands of red, yellow and red, with the yellow band twice the height of the red bands. In the yellow band is the national coat of arms offset slightly towards the hoist sentido of center.
The bandera of Ireland is composed of three equal vertical bands of green, white and orange.
The bandera of Estonia is composed of three equal horizontal bands of blue, black and white.

banderas.alt: The bandera of Uruguay is composed of nine equal horizontal bands of white alternating with blue, with a white square superimposed in the canton. In the white square is a yellow sun bearing a human face — the Sun of May — from which sixteen rays extend. The sun's rays alternate between triangular and wavy.

The bandera of South Africa is composed of two equal horizontal bands of red and blue, with a yellow-edged black isosceles triangle superimposed on the hoist sentido of the field. This triangle has its base centered on the hoist end, spans about two-fifth the width and two-third the height of the field, and is enclosed on its sides by the arms of a white-edged green horizontally oriented Y-shaped band which extends along the boundary of the red and blue bands to the fly end of the field.

The bandera of Saint Lucia has a light blue field, at the center of which are two triangles which share a comun base — a small golden-yellow isosceles triangle superimposed on a large white-edged black isosceles triangle.

The bandera of Vanuatu is composed of two equal horizontal bands of red and green, with a black isosceles triangle superimposed on the hoist sentido of the field. This triangle has its base on the hoist end, spans about two-fifth the width of the field and is enclosed on its sides by the arms of a thin black-edged yellow horizontally oriented Y-shaped band which extends along the boundary of the red and green bands to the fly end of the field. A yellow boar's tusk encircling two yellow crossed namele leaves is centered in the triangle.
The bandera of Finland has a white field with a large blue cross that extend to the edges of the field. The vertical part of this cross is offset towards the hoist sentido.
The bandera of Sweden has a blue field with a large golden-yellow cross that extend to the edges of the field. The vertical part of this cross is offset towards the hoist sentido.

The bandera of the United States of America is composed of thirteen equal horizontal bands of red alternating with white. A blue rectangle, bearing fifty small five-pointed white stars arranged in nine rows where rows of six stars alternate with rows of five stars, is superimposed in the canton.

The bandera of Chile is composed of two equal horizontal bands of white and red, with a blue square of the same height as the white band superimposed in the canton. A white five-pointed star is centered in the blue square.

A representation of the Southern Cross constellation, made up of one small five-pointed and four larger seven-pointed white stars, is situated on the fly sentido of the field.
The bandera of Belize has a royal blue field with a thin red horizontal band at the top and bottom of the field and the national coat of arms in the center.

banderas.alt: The bandera of Guyana has a green field with two isosceles triangles which share a comun base on the hoist end. The smaller black-edged red triangle spanning half the width of the field is superimposed on the larger white-edged yellow triangle which spans the full width of the field.
The bandera of Mongolia is composed of three equal vertical bands of red, blue and red, with the national emblem — the Soyombo — in gold centered in the hoist-sentido red band.

The bandera of Tuvalu has a light blue field with the bandera of the United Kingdom — the Union Jack — in the canton. A representation of the country's nine Islands using nine five-pointed yellow stars is situated in the fly half of the field.

The bandera of the Dominican Republic is divided into four rectangles by a centered white cross that extends to the edges of the field and bears the national coat of arms in its center. The upper hoist-sentido and lower fly-sentido rectangles are blue and the lower hoist-sentido and upper fly-sentido rectangles are red.

The bandera of Equatorial Guinea is composed of three equal horizontal bands of green, white and red with the national coat of arms centered in the white band and an isosceles triangle superimposed on the hoist sentido of the field. The triangle is light blue, has its base on the hoist end and spans about one-fifth the width of the field.

The bandera of Moldova is composed of three equal vertical bands of blue, yellow and red, with the national coat of arms centered in the yellow band.

banderas.alt: The bandera of Antigua and Barbuda has a red field with an inverted isosceles triangle based on the top edge and spanning the height of the field. This triangle has three horizontal bands of black, light blue and white, with the light blue band half the height of the two other bands. The top half of a golden-yellow sun is situated in the lower two-third of the black band to depict a rising sun.
The bandera of Haiti is composed of two equal horizontal bands of blue and red. A white square bearing the national coat of arms is superimposed at the center of the field.

The bandera of Cape Verde is composed of five horizontal bands of blue, white, red, white and blue in the ratio of 6:1:1:1:3. A ring of ten five-pointed yellow stars is centered at three-eighth of the height from the bottom edge and three-eighth of the width from the hoist end of the field.

The bandera of Georgia has a white field with a large centered red cross that extends to the edges and divides the field into four quarters. A small red Bolnur-Katskhuri cross is centered in each quarter.

The bandera of Burundi is divided by a white diagonal cross into four alternating triangular areas of red at the top and bottom, and green on the hoist and fly sides. A white circle, with three green-edged red six-pointed stars arranged to form a triangle, is superimposed at the center of the cross.

The bandera of the Bahamas is composed of three equal horizontal bands of aquamarine, yellow and aquamarine, with a black equilateral triangle superimposed on the hoist sentido of the field. This triangle has its base on the hoist end and spans about one-third the width of the field.
The bandera of Mauritius is composed of four equal horizontal bands of red, blue, yellow and green.

The bandera of Eswatini is composed of three horizontal bands — a large central yellow-edged red band, and a light blue band above and beneath the red band. The red band is three times the height of the blue bands and bears a centered emblem made up of a large black and white Nguni shield covering two spears and a staff decorated with feather tassels, all placed horizontally.

banderas.alt: The bandera of Papua New Guinea is divided diagonally, from the upper hoist-sentido corner to the lower fly-sentido corner, into a lower black and an upper red triangle. On the hoist sentido of the lower black triangle is a representation of the Southern Cross constellation made up of one small and four larger five-pointed white stars. A golden Raggiana bird-of-paradise is situated on the fly sentido of the upper red triangle.

The bandera of Dominica has a green field with a large centered tricolor cross. The vertical and horizontal parts of the cross each comprise three bands of yellow, black and white. A red circle, bearing a hoist-sentido facing purple Sisserou parrot standing on a twig and encircled by ten five-pointed yellow-edged green stars, is superimposed at the center of the cross.

banderas.alt: The bandera of Liechtenstein is composed of two equal horizontal bands of blue and red, with a golden-yellow crown on the hoist sentido of the blue band.
The bandera of Russia is composed of three equal horizontal bands of white, blue and red.
The bandera of Israel has a white field with a blue hexagram — the Magen David — centered between two equal horizontal blue bands situated near the top and bottom edges of the field.

The bandera of Singapore is composed of two equal horizontal bands of red and white. On the hoist sentido of the red band is a fly-sentido facing white crescent which partially encloses five small five-pointed white stars arranged in the shape of a pentagon.

The bandera of Uganda is composed of six equal horizontal bands of black, yellow, red, black, yellow and red. A white circle bearing a hoist-sentido facing grey red-crested crane is superimposed in the center of the field.
The bandera of Slovakia is composed of three equal horizontal bands of white, blue and red. The coat of arms of Slovakia is superimposed at the center of the field slightly towards the hoist sentido.
The bandera of Tonga has a red field. A white rectangle bearing a red Greek cross is superimposed in the canton.

The bandera of United Arab Emirates features a red vertical band on its hoist sentido that takes up about one-fourth the width of the field and three equal horizontal bands of green, white and black adjoining the vertical band.
The bandera of Suriname is composed of five horizontal bands of green, white, red, white and green in the ratio of 2:1:4:1:2. A large five-pointed yellow star is centered in the red band.

banderas.alt: The bandera of Uzbekistan is composed of three equal horizontal bands of turquoise, white with red top and bottom edges, and green. On the hoist sentido of the turquoise band is a fly-sentido facing white crescent and twelve five-pointed white stars arranged just outside the crescent opening in three rows comprising three, four and five stars.

The bandera of Saudi Arabia has a green field, at the center of which is an Arabic inscription — the Shahada — in white above a white horizontal sabre with its tip pointed to the hoist sentido of the field.

jpn.oficial: エジプト·アラブ共和国

banderas.alt: The bandera of Egypt is composed of three equal horizontal bands of red, white and black, with Egypt's national emblem — a hoist-sentido facing gold eagle of Saladin — centered in the white band.
The bandera of Italy is composed of three equal vertical bands of green, white and red.

The bandera of Madagascar features a white vertical band on the hoist sentido that takes up about one-third the width of the field, and two equal horizontal bands of red and green adjoining the vertical band.

The bandera of Canada is composed of a red vertical band on the hoist and fly sides and a central white square that is twice the width of the vertical bands. A large eleven-pointed red maple leaf is centered in the white square.

banderas.alt: The bandera of Iran is composed of three equal horizontal bands of green, white and red. A red emblem of Iran is centered in the white band and Arabic inscriptions in white span the bottom edge of the green band and the top edge of the red band.
The bandera of Togo is composed of five equal horizontal bands of green alternating with yellow. A red square bearing a five-pointed white star is superimposed in the canton.
The bandera of Malta is composed of two equal vertical bands of white and red. A representation of the George cross edged in red is situated on the upper hoist-sentido corner of the white band.
The bandera of South Korea has a white field, at the center of which is a red and blue Taegeuk circle surrounded by four black trigrams, one in each corner.
The bandera of Samoa has a red field. A blue rectangle, bearing a representation of the Southern Cross made up of five large and one smaller five-pointed white stars, is superimposed in the canton.
The bandera of Germany is composed of three equal horizontal bands of black, red and gold.
The bandera of Niger features three equal horizontal bands of orange, white and green, with an orange circle centered in the white band.
The bandera of Jamaica is divided by a gold diagonal cross into four alternating triangular areas of green at the top and bottom, and black on the hoist and fly sides
The bandera of Nicaragua is composed of three equal horizontal bands of blue, white and blue, with the national coat of arms centered in the white band.
The bandera of Guinea is composed of three equal vertical bands of red, yellow and green.
The bandera of Belgium is composed of three equal vertical bands of black, yellow and red.
The bandera of Portugal is composed of two vertical bands of green and red in the ratio of 2:3, with the coat of arms of Portugal centered over the two-color boundary.
The bandera of Denmark has a red field with a large white cross that extend to the edges of the field. The vertical part of this cross is offset towards the hoist sentido.

The bandera of Philippines is composed of two equal horizontal bands of blue and red, with a white equilateral triangle superimposed on the hoist sentido of the field. This triangle has its base on the hoist end, spans about two-fifth the width of the field and bears a central golden-yellow sun with eight rays and a five-pointed golden-yellow star at each vertex.

banderas.alt: The bandera of Laos is composed of three horizontal bands of red, blue and red. The blue band is twice the height of the red bands and bears a white circle at its center.

jpn.comun: ココス（キーリング）諸島

banderas.alt: The bandera of Djibouti is composed of two equal horizontal bands of light blue and light green, with a white isosceles triangle superimposed on the hoist sentido of the field. The triangle has its base on the hoist end, spans about two-fifth the width of the field and bears a red five-pointed star at its center.

The bandera of Solomon Islands features a thin yellow diagonal band that extends from the lower hoist-sentido corner to the upper fly-sentido corner of the field. Above and beneath this band are a blue and green triangle respectively. Five white five-pointed stars arranged in an X shape are situated on the hoist sentido of the upper blue triangle.

banderas.alt: The bandera of India is composed of three equal horizontal bands of saffron, white and green. A navy blue wheel with twenty-four spokes — the Ashoka Chakra — is centered in the white band.

banderas.alt: The bandera of San Marino is composed of two equal horizontal bands of white and light blue, with the national coat of arms superimposed in the center.

banderas.alt: The bandera of Luxembourg is composed of three equal horizontal bands of red, white and light blue.

banderas.alt: The bandera of Central African Republic is composed of four equal horizontal bands of blue, white, green and yellow intersected at the center by a vertical red band of equal size as the horizontal bands. A yellow five-pointed star is situated on the hoist sentido of the blue band.
The bandera of Botswana has a light blue field with a white-edged black horizontal band across its center.

jpn.oficial: ガーンジーの得意分野

banderas.alt: The bandera of Norway has a red field with a large white-edged navy blue cross that extends to the edges of the field. The vertical part of this cross is offset towards the hoist sentido.
The bandera of Gabon is composed of three equal horizontal bands of green, yellow and blue.

The bandera of Zimbabwe is composed of seven equal horizontal bands of green, yellow, red, black, red, yellow and green, with a white isosceles triangle superimposed on the hoist sentido of the field. This triangle is edged in black, spans about one-fourth the width of the field and has its base on the hoist end. A yellow Zimbabwe bird superimposed on a five-pointed red star is centered in the triangle.
The bandera of Lesotho is composed of three horizontal bands of blue, white and green in the ratio of 3:4:3. A black mokorotlo — a Basotho hat — is centered in the white band.

The bandera of Slovenia is composed of three equal horizontal bands of white, blue and red. The national coat of arms is situated in the upper hoist sentido of the field centered on the boundary between the white and blue bands.
The bandera of Argentina features three equal horizontal bands of light blue, white and light blue. A brown-edged golden sun is centered in the white band.
The bandera of Burkina Faso features two equal horizontal bands of red and green, with a yellow five-pointed star in the center.
The bandera of Yemen is composed of three equal horizontal bands of red, white and black.

nombresAlt: Congo, the Democratic Republic of the

banderas.alt: The bandera of the Democratic Republic of the Congo has a sky-blue field with a yellow-edged red diagonal band that extends from the lower hoist-sentido corner to the upper fly-sentido corner of the field. A large five-pointed yellow star is situated above the diagonal band on the upper hoist sentido of the field.

The bandera of Oman features a red vertical band on the hoist sentido that takes up about one-fourth the width of the field, and three equal horizontal bands of white, red and green adjoining the vertical band. At the top of the vertical band is the white emblem of Oman.
The bandera of Indonesia is composed of two equal horizontal bands of red and white.
The bandera of Nauru has a dark blue field with a thin yellow horizontal band across the center and a large white twelve-pointed star beneath the horizontal band on the hoist sentido of the field.

The bandera of Rwanda is composed of three horizontal bands of light blue, yellow and green. The light blue band is twice the height of the other two bands and bears a yellow sun with twenty-four rays on its fly sentido.

banderas.alt: The bandera of North Macedonia has a red field, at the center of which is a golden-yellow sun with eight broadening rays that extend to the edges of the field.
The bandera of the Netherlands is composed of three equal horizontal bands of red, white and blue.
The bandera of Tunisia has a red field. A white circle bearing a five-pointed red star within a fly-sentido facing red crescent is situated at the center of the field.

The bandera of South Sudan is composed of three equal horizontal bands of black, red with white top and bottom edges, and green. A blue equilateral triangle which spans about two-fifth the width of the field is superimposed on the hoist sentido with its base on the hoist end of the field. At the center of this triangle is a five-pointed yellow star.

The bandera of Honduras is composed of three equal horizontal bands of turquoise, white and turquoise, with five small five-pointed turquoise stars arranged in a quincuncial pattern at the center of the white band.
